The commemoration of the Battle of Isandlwana is underway in KZN. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The commemoration of the Battle of Isandlwana is underway in KZN. The event commemorates the nation's 1879 defeat of the British army on the Nquthu battlefields. READ:Â Legal battle over Zulu King's commemoration speech King MisuZulu kaZwelithini won a court battle trying to stop him delivering an address there. AmaZulu traditional Prime Minister Mangosuthu Buthelezi says the nation needs his leadership. Buthelezi said, "today [Saturday] the King will speak about lessons as is his duty." "We are blessed to have a guidance of a King at this time to strengthen our nation, we as Zulu people have a King the only thing that still needs to be done is for the president to officiate [and] acknowledge that, the king is not voted for. He is appointed by his father right through."